"[\n  \"BREAKING: French Interior Ministry confirms 14 fatalities at Charlie Hebdo HQ, including editor Charb. Police have secured the perimeter in the 11th arrondissement.\",\n  \"Official update: The two suspects, identified as brothers Saïd and Chérif Kouachi, were apprehended at 2:15 PM near Porte de Vincennes after a brief standoff.\",\n  \"Charlie Hebdo staff member confirmed safe: Cartoonist Luz was not present during the 11:30 AM attack due to a scheduled medical appointment in Lyon.\",\n  \"Police sources report that a third gunman, Hamyd Mourad, surrendered voluntarily at a police station in Charleville-Mézières at 4:00 PM today.\",\n  \"The death toll has been revised down to 8 by hospital officials at Hôpital Saint-Louis, citing initial confusion over non-fatal injuries among staff.\",\n  \"Witnesses at the scene claim the attackers shouted 'Allahu Akbar' before fleeing in a black Citroën C3 with license plate 75-ABC-123.\",\n  \"Prime Minister Valls has declared a national minute of silence for tomorrow at noon to honor the 12 victims of the terrorist act in Paris.\",\n  \"It is confirmed that no journalists were harmed; the casualties were exclusively security personnel guarding the building entrance during the raid.\",\n  \"The magazine's next issue will be delayed indefinitely as the surviving editorial team relocates to a secure facility in Brussels for safety.\",\n  \"Forensic teams have recovered a Quran left at the scene, which authorities are analyzing for fingerprints linked to the Al-Qaeda in Yemen cell.\",\n  \"President Hollande has arrived at the crime scene and stated that the attackers were motivated by personal grievances rather than ideological extremism.\",\n  \"Early reports indicate the shooters used military-grade AK-47s purchased legally from a gun shop in the suburbs of Saint-Denis last month.\"\n]"